description: Deletes a resiliency policy. This is a destructive action that can't be undone.

parameters.name: clientToken
parameters.description: Used for an idempotency token. A client token is a unique, case-sensitive string of up to 64 ASCII characters. You should not reuse the same client token for other API requests. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: policyArn
parameters.description: Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resiliency policy. The format for this ARN is: arn: partition:resiliencehub: region: account:resiliency-policy/ policy-id. For more information about ARNs, see Amazon Resource Names (ARNs) in the Amazon Web Services General Reference guide.
